## PROJECT OVERVIEW
This is a real-time voice AI sales agent for the Commercial Real Estate (CRE)
technology market. Jordan — our AI agent — conducts live voice conversations
with CRE brokers, handles objections, calls tools mid-conversation, and closes
deals. Everything runs in Python. No databases, no RAG, no external speech
services.

## CRITICAL RULES — NEVER VIOLATE THESE

### Audio
- INPUT_RATE  = 16000   # microphone — Gemini expected input
- OUTPUT_RATE = 24000   # speaker — Gemini outputs 24kHz, NOT 16kHz
- OUTPUT_CHUNK = 1024   # max buffer size for clean interruption cutoff
- Never change OUTPUT_RATE to 16000. Audio will be slow and distorted.
- On interruption signal: call output_stream.stop_stream() immediately, drain buffer

### Config
- ALL product data (plans, pricing, competitors, ROI) lives in config.json ONLY
- tools.py must read from CONFIG = json.load(open('config.json')) at module level
- Never hardcode plan names, prices, or competitor data in Python files
- Never hardcode the product name — always read from config['agent']['company']
- Product name placeholder is [PRODUCT_NAME] — will be replaced via config.json

### Prompt
- Never edit prompts/system_prompt.txt manually — it is auto-generated
- Always re-run generate_prompt.py after any config.json change
- Prompt must use contractions throughout (I'm, it's, you'll, that's)
- Prompt must never contain markdown symbols (* # -) — Gemini reads them aloud

### Tools
- Every ADK tool function must have a docstring — ADK uses it to decide when to call
- Every tool write to dashboard_state must use _lock from state.py
- Every tool call must append to dashboard_state['tools_called']

### Architecture
- agent.py and vision.py run locally ONLY — they need mic/speaker
- server.py + dashboard.html deploy to Google Cloud Run
- Dockerfile must NOT include agent.py or vision.py

## FILE RESPONSIBILITIES

agent.py
  - Entry point only
  - Startup sequence: generate_prompt() → start server thread → connect Gemini → start audio threads → start vision thread
  - Audio loop: base on Google SDK reference example, do not invent
  - Print on ready: "Jordan from [config agent company] is ready. Start speaking."

config.json
  - Single source of truth for all domain data
  - Structure: agent{}, plans[], competitors[], roi_data{}
  - Changing this file + rerunning generate_prompt.py = full domain swap

generate_prompt.py
  - Reads config.json
  - Writes prompts/system_prompt.txt
  - Must log approximate token count to console
  - Run automatically at agent.py startup

tools.py
  - 6 functions: get_product_info, calculate_price, compare_competitor,
    generate_recommendation, update_customer_profile, update_sales_stage
  - All read from CONFIG (loaded at module level)
  - All write to state via state._lock

state.py
  - Single shared dict: dashboard_state
  - Keys: stage, stage_history, profile, tools_called, strategy
  - All mutations use threading.Lock

server.py
  - FastAPI on port 8080
  - GET /         → serve dashboard.html
  - GET /state    → return dashboard_state as JSON
  - POST /update_state → update in-memory state
  - GET /health   → {status: ok, timestamp: unix_time}
  - CORS: allow all origins

vision.py
  - cv2.VideoCapture(0)
  - 1 frame per 1.5 seconds
  - JPEG quality 70
  - Entire function wrapped in try/except — fail silently
  - Daemon thread always

dashboard.html
  - Single file — no external CSS/JS files
  - Dark theme: #0F172A bg, #E2E8F0 text, #3B82F6 accent
  - 2x2 CSS grid, min 18px font everywhere
  - Poll GET /state every 1000ms
  - Stage badge colors: DISCOVERY=#3B82F6, PITCH=#22C55E, OBJECTION_HANDLING=#F97316, CLOSING=#A855F7
  - Yellow flash (#FEF08A) on new profile entries

## CRE DOMAIN CONTEXT

The pain: CRE brokers manually pull comparable sales from CoStar → paste into Excel
→ format report → email to client. This takes 2-4 hours per report.
[PRODUCT_NAME] automates this in under 60 seconds.

Jordan's opening question: "Are you more focused on the transaction side or asset management?"
This single question segments the prospect and establishes CRE credibility.

Key signals Jordan listens for:
- "CoStar and Excel" → core pain confirmed → skip to PITCH on comp automation
- "CoStar" as competitor → not a competitor, complementary: "[PRODUCT_NAME] sits on top of CoStar"
- Team size mentioned → call update_customer_profile immediately
- Shows something on webcam → react to it before anything else

## ADK TOOL BEHAVIOR

Tools are conversation pivots, not just data lookups. Each call changes
what Jordan does next.

generate_recommendation logic:
  team <= 3  → Starter ($299/mo)
  team <= 15 → Professional ($799/mo)
  team > 15  → Enterprise ($1,999/mo)
  Adjust: if 'comp_analysis' or 'reporting' in pain_points → push toward Professional minimum

compare_competitor for CoStar:
  NEVER position as competitive. Always: "We sit on top of CoStar, your
  subscription stays, it becomes 10x more productive."

## SALES STAGE RULES

Stage transitions are INTENT-driven, not timer-driven.

GREETING → DISCOVERY: when customer answers the opening CRE question
DISCOVERY → PITCH: only when Jordan knows team_size + current_workflow + primary_pain
PITCH → OBJECTION_HANDLING: when customer signals an objection
OBJECTION_HANDLING → PITCH or CLOSING: only when objection is fully resolved
CLOSING: when customer asks for recommendation or signals purchase intent

## VOICE QUALITY NON-NEGOTIABLES
- Voice: Aoede (primary) or Puck — set in PrebuiltVoiceConfig
- Contractions always: "I'm" not "I am", "it's" not "it is"
- Max 2 clauses per sentence
- No bullet reading — lists must be converted to natural speech
- Forbidden words: firstly, secondly, in conclusion, leverage, synergy, circle back
- CRE vocabulary used naturally: comps, NOI, cap rate, pipeline, close rate
- Filler transitions: "so", "here's the thing", "actually", "right"

